,Recommended,539720,32578833,Posted: 19 June,all,gyashaa,"Pros:- Looks good- Great music- Decent Gameplay (not great, but not bad)Cons:- DifficultThe problems:- You can't see very far ahead so you don't have much time to react. An option to change field of view would be nice.- On top of the little reaction time, the car turns very slowly. This makes it difficult and sometimes even impossible to grab items or get out of the way of other vehicles. An option to change turning speed and an option to turn with the mouse would be great.- Menu options are unclear with just symbols instead of words or abbreviations- Menu options counterintuitive. e.g. pressing escape pauses the game but pressing escape again doesn't unpause the game, it brings you back to the main menu and erases any progress you have made, without any warning. Wtf.- Needs options to change volume of music and sfx- Could just be me but I feel like in the later levers (5 and up) you lose gas too quickly. I also think you should lose gas slower when not using the accelerator.- The buffs (speed boost, invulnerability, slow down) don't last very longExtras ideas:- Would love to be able to reverse (to grab a buff or gas that I missed). Technically you 'can' but you can only go reeeeeeeeeally slow. Also, you're quickly and constantly losing gas so pretty much you WILL lose all of your gas (and the game) before you ever reach the item.- The only difference between the unlockable cars is how they look (which isn't ""bad""), but maybe you can have the different cars have different strengths and weaknesses. i.e. one car drives super fast, another car turns fast, another is slow but can recover more easily when hitting another car, etc. So many possibilities.- Could use more variety of buffs. Extra lives, extra score points, temporary infinite gas, etcOverall, it's a pretty decent casual/arcade game. I recommend it if you're into 80s music and visuals.And to the devs, thank you for putting the soundtrack up for download. I was actually going to request it before it was up. :)"
