76561198043933101,Recommended,539720,34725288,Posted: 3 September,all,therob,"Oldschool car game with neon coloring and different vehicles & colored stages to unlock.  This is a cheap & easy game to 100%.  It may take about half an hour to collect the first 8 achievements.  They unlock as you accumulate more and more miles on the track.  The 9th achievement is a little harder since you will have to be savvy with how the game works and be able to get to level 10.  It took me about 1 hour to do this for a total of 1.5 hours to 100% it.  However, there are 5 cards to unlock while playing and it may take 2.5-3 hours to unlock all 5 cards.  Definitely get this if you're trying to up your achievement stats."
76561197971341065,Not Recommended,539720,29554468,Posted: 28 January,all,sfnhltb,"A top down racing game where you have to avoid crashing into the walls (and if going more than medium pace, cars which spin you into walls if you hit them) and run over the petrol pumps to extend your timer - while it seems like it should be a fuel gauge, it goes down at the same speed whether you are going top speed or crawling along at a snails pace, so functionally it is a timer. This gives the odd situation that if you are running low on ""fuel"" you have to nail the accelerator in the hope you make it to the next fuel station in time.The early levels (1-4) play quite well, you can go flat out in light traffic, and the challenge of hitting at least every third or so fuel pump while also avoiding cars makes for quite a good balance. This all starts to fall apart from the 5th level with the combination of regular narrow 2 lane sections that make it impossible not to slow down to a much more sedate pace, plus a new type of car in the traffic that bounces from wall to wall, which are bad enough to deal with in the full width sections, but basically make going any faster than about 150 suicidal from that point on.If you can make it pootling along to level 10-11 it then gets worse, as you end up stuck on an almost continuously 2 narrow lane setup, which briefly widens regularly but no usually long enough to overtake anything. Meanwhile a mass of purple cars that all go the same speed and move to block you appear and quickly there are dozens of them making it impossible to do anything but chug along behind them at a tepid pace.Overall I can't really recommend this, if the difficulty of the traffic ramped up slowly following the patterns at the beginning of the game it could have been fairly decent, but everything after that is poor and gets worse. Also this game randomly appeared in my games list a few weeks back, and I have no idea why - was it meant to be a free review copy, not sure."
